;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Seminar&gt; Students will develop the ability to discuss a topic with a group. The topics will challenge students to think beyond their experiences and cultural influences.</span></span></span></div><div><br /></div>", "授業外学習2": "<div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Reading&gt; Students read short texts and complete language development activities. They read graded readers for fluency and speed.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Seminar&gt; Students will engage with test materials to prepare for class. Students learn vocabulary from the materials to ask discussion questions and use discussion skills. Students ﬁnd information on the Internet and evaluate it.</span></span></span></div>"}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Materials will be available on LUNA. You should bring your materials to class on your device (computer/tablet). Students will also be required to purchase an XReading card."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Conducted in class"], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students1": ["Each class subject is arranged on the curriculum based on the Diploma Policy (DP) and Curriculum Policy (CP) established by each faculty and graduate school. By studying this course with DP/CP in mind, you will develop the abilities expected by each faculty and graduate school. The DP, CP, and curriculum table (list of classes, etc.) for each faculty/graduate school are posted in the link below, so please use them as a reference for your study plan. https://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1 *Link to kwic (only current students can view)"], "成績評価Grading0": 